591
00:27:44,163 --> 00:27:45,997
Didn't the radiation work?

592
00:27:46,623 --> 00:27:48,833
It did what it was
supposed to do.

593
00:27:52,588 --> 00:27:53,921
You're dying.

594
00:27:55,966 --> 00:27:58,885
What do you mean? Like things are bad
and that someday I'm gonna...

595
00:28:00,971 --> 00:28:05,975
How much time?

596
00:28:06,101 --> 00:28:07,060
We can't know exactly.

597
00:28:07,186 --> 00:28:08,436
A year?

598
00:28:10,189 --> 00:28:11,606
Less than a year?

599
00:28:12,107 --> 00:28:13,608
Less than 24 hours.

600
00:28:14,777 --> 00:28:16,235
I don't understand.

601
00:28:16,362 --> 00:28:18,905
Why are you saying this to me?
You're trying to scare me?

602
00:28:19,031 --> 00:28:20,365
Why would you do that?

603
00:28:20,574 --> 00:28:21,616
I'm sorry.

604
00:28:21,742 --> 00:28:22,909
It's true.

605
00:28:23,285 --> 00:28:27,497
How bad is this cancer?
Yesterday you thought I had a chance.

606
00:28:27,831 --> 00:28:29,499
You don't have cancer.

607
00:28:31,085 --> 00:28:32,835
You came in with an infection.

608
00:28:34,004 --> 00:28:36,631
- We didn't catch it.
- What kind of infection?

609
00:28:36,757 --> 00:28:37,590
Doesn't matter.

610
00:28:39,218 --> 00:28:42,345
Radiation was the worst thing
we could have done.

611
00:28:43,138 --> 00:28:45,848
We destroyed the part of your body
that was fighting it off.

612
00:28:46,725 --> 00:28:47,892
It's spread to your heart.

613
00:28:48,018 --> 00:28:49,894
Then give me drugs.

614
00:28:50,020 --> 00:28:51,270
They have drugs for infections.

615
00:28:51,397 --> 00:28:53,773
Antibiotics work
with the immune system,

616
00:28:53,899 --> 00:28:56,901
but your immune system
is nonexistent because of the radiation.

617
00:28:57,027 --> 00:29:00,488
If it's my heart,
you can get me a new heart.

618
00:29:00,614 --> 00:29:02,824
People have heart transplants
all the time!

619
00:29:02,950 --> 00:29:04,200
It wouldn't help.

620
00:29:06,078 --> 00:29:08,413
The infection's everywhere.

621
00:29:10,999 --> 00:29:14,544
There's nothing anybody can do.

622
00:29:25,431 --> 00:29:26,597
I'm so sorry.

623
00:29:32,563 --> 00:29:34,605
We'll call your grandparents.

624
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:39,944
Get the hell away from me!
Get out!

625
00:29:40,070 --> 00:29:41,154
Get out!

626
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:23,321
I think it's broken.

627
00:30:23,447 --> 00:30:26,532
Nothing like a melodramatic
gesture to solve everything.

628
00:30:26,658 --> 00:30:28,778
We were wrong, too.
Steroids wouldn't have helped her.

629
00:30:28,869 --> 00:30:31,996
I didn't not help her.
I actually pulled the trigger.

630
00:30:32,122 --> 00:30:34,373
There's nothing left
for you to do.

631
00:30:34,500 --> 00:30:35,458
One of us could go home with...

632
00:30:35,584 --> 00:30:37,126
You're trying to
make me feel better?

633
00:30:37,252 --> 00:30:39,170
- Yeah.
- I killed a woman.

634
00:30:39,296 --> 00:30:40,536
Don't you think
it's appropriate

635
00:30:40,547 --> 00:30:43,216
I feel like crap
for at least a little while?

636
00:30:43,342 --> 00:30:45,301
It won't help her.

637
00:30:48,764 --> 00:30:49,805
Where is he?

638
00:30:49,932 --> 00:30:51,182
He went to the ICU.

639
00:30:57,147 --> 00:30:59,148
What are you doing?

640
00:30:59,274 --> 00:31:00,816
Prepping for an aspiration.

641
00:31:00,943 --> 00:31:02,151
We still don't know
what infection...

642
00:31:02,277 --> 00:31:03,110
It's not gonna help her.

643
00:31:03,237 --> 00:31:04,487
It's not gonna hurt her.

644
00:31:04,613 --> 00:31:05,947
Well, it is gonna hurt her
but it's not gonna...

645
00:31:06,073 --> 00:31:07,114
No.

646
00:31:07,783 --> 00:31:08,783
This'll just take
a few minutes.

647
00:31:08,909 --> 00:31:09,867
I'll grab a piece
of an abscess,

648
00:31:09,993 --> 00:31:11,536
- some pus...
- You really don't care.

649
00:31:11,662 --> 00:31:13,463
You really don't care
why she's gonna be dead.

650
00:31:13,622 --> 00:31:14,822
She's gonna be dead because...

651
00:31:14,915 --> 00:31:15,915
What?

652
00:31:17,626 --> 00:31:20,753
What did we screw up?
What did we miss?

653
00:31:22,339 --> 00:31:23,881
I need to know.

654
00:31:25,092 --> 00:31:26,133
You'll have to wait.

655
00:31:35,769 --> 00:31:37,186
We're moving her back
to her room.

656
00:31:37,312 --> 00:31:40,439
Patients who've had total body radiation
have to stay in ICU.

657
00:31:40,566 --> 00:31:42,149
ICU isn't going to help her.

658
00:31:42,276 --> 00:31:43,397
Let's give her some privacy.

659
00:31:55,956 --> 00:31:57,873
What do you want?

660
00:31:58,584 --> 00:32:00,501
Want to see
if I'm dying on schedule?

661
00:32:03,880 --> 00:32:06,090
Or do you want me
to tell you it's all right,

662
00:32:06,216 --> 00:32:07,341
I'm okay with it?

663
00:32:08,260 --> 00:32:11,554
I'd like your forgiveness.
I don't expect it.

664
00:32:12,889 --> 00:32:14,140
Good.

665
00:32:14,266 --> 00:32:18,060
'Cause this isn't like you ran your cart
into mine at the supermarket.

666
00:32:18,979 --> 00:32:20,187
No.

667
00:32:21,064 --> 00:32:22,982
Your grandparents
haven't arrived yet.

668
00:32:23,984 --> 00:32:26,152
If they don't make it on time,

669
00:32:27,112 --> 00:32:29,113
is there anything
you'd like me to tell them?

670
00:32:29,239 --> 00:32:30,489
I never really knew them.

671
00:32:32,451 --> 00:32:35,161
You got any friends
you want me to call?

672
00:32:36,496 --> 00:32:37,955
It's the middle of the night.

673
00:32:38,915 --> 00:32:41,334
They're not the kind of friends you ask
to help you move,

674
00:32:41,460 --> 00:32:43,919
never mind watch you die.

675
00:32:47,007 --> 00:32:48,507
I never did much.

676
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:51,886
No kid to leave behind.

677
00:32:53,930 --> 00:32:56,515
When I go, the world's
not gonna be any different.

678
00:32:58,977 --> 00:33:01,771
Kind of a relief for you, huh?

679
00:33:41,728 --> 00:33:44,522
You were right about me.

680
00:33:45,107 --> 00:33:46,941
Yeah? Which time?

681
00:33:51,988 --> 00:33:53,989
I had a problem with you.

682
00:33:57,202 --> 00:33:58,869
But you were wrong, too.

683
00:34:00,288 --> 00:34:02,248
I've made some bad decisions.

684
00:34:03,667 --> 00:34:06,460
Stole cars. Robbed houses.

685
00:34:07,379 --> 00:34:08,587
Killed a woman.

686
00:34:13,385 --> 00:34:14,844
But then I got another chance.

687
00:34:16,263 --> 00:34:20,266
Left home, went to college,
entered a whole other world.

688
00:34:21,017 --> 00:34:24,895
And there's some part of me
I can't get rid of, always thinks,

689
00:34:25,689 --> 00:34:31,318
if I'm not the smartest,
if I'm not the first, everywhere I go

690
00:34:32,988 --> 00:34:35,197
they'll figure out
I'm not supposed to be here.

691
00:34:37,117 --> 00:34:38,492
They'll send me back.

692
00:34:39,619 --> 00:34:41,412
You know that's
not gonna happen.

693
00:34:41,997 --> 00:34:42,997
You're out.

694
00:34:43,123 --> 00:34:44,582
I'll never be out of there.

695
00:34:48,253 --> 00:34:51,881
When I came home that last Christmas
I was in college,

696
00:34:52,924 --> 00:34:55,426
it was like the rooms

697
00:34:56,678 --> 00:34:58,971
felt so small.

698
00:35:00,015 --> 00:35:01,432
It was suffocating.

699
00:35:02,350 --> 00:35:05,603
But when I was standing
on the stoop saying goodbye,

700
00:35:07,105 --> 00:35:08,939
my mom put her arms around me.

701
00:35:12,944 --> 00:35:14,487
That was...

702
00:35:15,322 --> 00:35:17,573
That was the last time
I ever felt at home.

703
00:35:24,080 --> 00:35:26,874
I only put distance

704
00:35:28,168 --> 00:35:31,545
between you and me because I know
there isn't any.

705
00:35:33,965 --> 00:35:35,966
You were right about me, too.

706
00:35:39,054 --> 00:35:44,058
That stuff about the system being
against people like me...

707
00:35:44,184 --> 00:35:46,602
I know it's crap.

708
00:35:46,728 --> 00:35:50,523
I mean, it's true
but it's also crap.

709
00:35:51,358 --> 00:35:55,528
I just wasn't ready
to try again.

710
00:35:56,863 --> 00:35:59,782
But I always thought
I was young.

711
00:36:01,159 --> 00:36:02,952
I had time.

712
00:36:17,801 --> 00:36:20,177
Aren't you ever gonna leave?

713
00:36:21,513 --> 00:36:22,680
No.

714
00:36:56,840 --> 00:37:00,551
- Yeah?
- Time of death, 3:35.

715
00:37:00,969 --> 00:37:02,177
Do whatever you want.

716
00:37:31,958 --> 00:37:34,209
You wanna go and get drunk?

717
00:37:34,336 --> 00:37:35,461
No, thanks.

718
00:37:36,004 --> 00:37:37,546
I've got paperwork.

719
00:37:42,177 --> 00:37:43,761
Listen, I don't...

720
00:37:43,887 --> 00:37:46,805
I don't know what I believe
but sometimes I need to think

721
00:37:46,932 --> 00:37:48,933
there's something out there
paying attention.

722
00:37:50,018 --> 00:37:51,602
So when I can't
talk to anybody,

723
00:37:51,728 --> 00:37:55,648
I talk to God and pretend
somebody's listening.

724
00:37:57,943 --> 00:37:59,985
We were all wrong. You know?

725
00:38:00,904 --> 00:38:02,237
Even House was wrong.

726
00:38:04,741 --> 00:38:05,783
I know.

727
00:38:51,955 --> 00:38:54,164
I got your consent.

728
00:38:56,835 --> 00:38:58,335
Her bra hook.

729
00:38:59,170 --> 00:39:00,587
What?

730
00:39:00,714 --> 00:39:03,090
She scratched herself
with her bra hook.

731
00:39:06,094 --> 00:39:08,178
That's how
the infection got in.

732
00:39:16,354 --> 00:39:17,896
Staph aureus.

733
00:39:19,899 --> 00:39:22,276
She died from a simple
staph infection?

734
00:39:23,778 --> 00:39:26,196
That and some bad decisions.

735
00:39:34,039 --> 00:39:35,831
I'll be outside.

736
00:39:50,388 --> 00:39:53,932
Go home. Have a few drinks.
Go to sleep.

737
00:39:54,059 --> 00:39:57,311
Get up tomorrow.
And do it all over.

738
00:39:57,437 --> 00:39:58,270
Only better.

739
00:40:00,982 --> 00:40:03,567
If you need absolution,
go to a priest

740
00:40:04,527 --> 00:40:06,779
or give alms to the poor.

741
00:40:07,739 --> 00:40:09,615
Whatever ritual comforts you.

742
00:40:10,033 --> 00:40:11,700
I killed her.

743
00:40:12,952 --> 00:40:14,244
Yeah. Me, too.

744
00:40:15,455 --> 00:40:18,707
This wasn't, "Oh, I should've thought
of that idea sooner."

745
00:40:19,542 --> 00:40:21,835
This wasn't messing up
a dosage!

746
00:40:21,961 --> 00:40:24,713
We see a disease rushing down
on someone like a train,

747
00:40:25,173 --> 00:40:26,840
we can't always get them
out of the way!

748
00:40:28,843 --> 00:40:30,761
But this wasn't that.

749
00:40:32,013 --> 00:40:33,013
No.

750
00:40:34,140 --> 00:40:35,933
And you'll do it again.

751
00:40:38,853 --> 00:40:42,147
For a lot of doctors,

752
00:40:42,273 --> 00:40:46,151
this would be
a once-in-a-lifetime mistake.

753
00:40:47,403 --> 00:40:49,154
But we're not a lot of doctors.

754
00:40:50,073 --> 00:40:53,033
And we'll save more patients
than the guy down the street

755
00:40:53,993 --> 00:40:54,827
but a few of the ones
that he'd save

756
00:40:54,953 --> 00:40:58,705
by doing what
everyone else does, we will lose.

